Fred was playing with his regular partner, ^*BBrad Moss^*N, when this week's deal was played. Despite Fred's poor bidding and play on this deal, his team (which also included ^*BJohn Carruthers^*N and ^*BHoward Weinstein^*N) went on the win the ^*BNations Cup^*N. This was a pretty exciting event to win because the other 3 teams that participated were representing 3 of the strongest bridge-playing countries in the world: Italy, Poland, and The Netherlands.

Fred and Brad were playing against ^*BJan Jansma^*N and ^*BLouk Verhees^*N of The Netherlands in the final round of the ^*BNations Cup^*N when this weeks deal was played. Fred and Brad were very impressed by the strong play of this fine young pair as well as their excellent deportment at the table, even when the match was obviously going against them. We expect that you will be hearing the names Jansma and Verhees more and more in the years to come. This deal has been rotated to make South the declarer.




