nt|Fred chose to open 1@D (mostly because 1@D is the systemic opening with 4-4 in the minors for Fred and Brad). There is a good reason to consider opening 1@C with this particular hand. If partner has long diamonds and 4 or 5 points he will probably respond 1@D to 1@C, making it possible to reach a good 5@D, 6@D or 3NT. |
