nt|After a 1@D opening, however, if partner has a sub-minimum response with a long club suit, he is likely to pass and 1@D may well be the final contract. This benefit to opening 1@C is not exactly high frequency and there are some possible auctions in which opening 1@C with this pattern will lead to problems. Still, 1@C could easily be the winner at the table.|
